Hello y'all This place is pretty good! The price is right for the amount and quality. You get a lot of bang for your buck here and you should ask about their dinner specials. If you expect a Michelin star meal than that's on you. But this place is pretty good overall.

This is a good sushi restaurant for the area and it's a good price as well. The longest I've ever waited was about 25 minutes. The only thing is the vestibule to stand in is small. The overall feel of the restaurant is good, nothing spectacular to look at but there a quite a few guys making the sushi which is cool.
The bubble teas with tapioca are the best! 😍 I’ve never done reviews on restaurants but they definitely deserve it. The staff is really greaaat tooooo!!! Go check it out!!!

Have had takeout from here several times and never been disappointed, finally got an opportunity to eat in restaurant. They mostly do takeout and delivery, but there are a few booths and tables. We placed our order and paid at the counter, then took a seat. Water was brought and refilled, service was surprisingly attentive and food came out super fast. Portions were such that we had leftovers and there was no problem with anything we asked for. Garlic sauce had a little spice and was really garlicky, but not overpoweringly so. General Tso’s was really great, and potstickers taste homemade. Definitely my favorite Chinese restaurant in Chicago.

I rarely write reviews, but I love having this place in the neighborhood so thought I would share and hope to spread the word.  Have eaten in and taken out from Yummy many times, and have never been disappointed with any meal. The restaurant is clean and cozy, and the staff is friendly and service is prompt. I've had everything from the sushi to the traditional Chinese-American stuff (chicken, beef) and all cuisines have been excellent. Prices are more than reasonable, even a bargain, I would say.  This place is great and I highly recommend it to friends and family, and bring them here often. Will continue to do so!
Pretty cool place. There are two separate menus offering Japanese or Chinese food. The food was good as well!

Would rate 0 stars if I could. Never been satisfied with them whenever I order from them. Either they would forget part of my order or their food isn't up to par. Decided never to order from them again...

Order was sesame chicken with fries rice and crab rangoon/egg roll.  Egg roll was actually okay. Wasn't bland by any means but not great either. It's what you'd expect honestly.  Sesame chicken definitely did not use a sauce made from scratch. Very certain it's a sauce in a jar. Tasted very light but also too sweet for its color. The chicken was decently cooked.  The fried rice was a bit bland but a little soy sauce made it pretty good.  Now the upsetting part. The crab Rangoon here is very mediocre. Tasted weird and it explained the cheap price on it. I'm very sure these were frozen and store bought  3/5 at best. Not a bad place for the price.

I frequently order here and their miso soup, seaweed salad and sushi are AWESOME.  I also have tried their milk tea and it is so yummy, lol just like their name.  I have also had their shrimp and vegetable rolls and they are good as well.  Fast delivery, great prices and excellent food.  I love this place and will be enjoying their YUMMY food whenever I can!

So as we got up to put the menus back and we're walking out the door, a employee finally came out and asked can i help you. I said sorry been sitting here 10 minutes and left. And won't be back. Grubhub did say it would take about an hour for delivery..but that was a standard message and the delivery didn't take any longer. I also called the restaurant as time got closer to an hour of waiting just in case I too would have an order they wouldn't make, and all I received was an answer from a gentleman who was able to tell me based on my address that the delivery was five minutes away (out of the 15 min dist from my house..) and he was exact. Food was great, though I always get spicy salmon, so who can complain? Oh and the delivery lady was super conscious and sweet. :) Thank you!!

I ordered through Grub-hub and was having my food delivered to my work. My office is a building with our name large and clear on the front, not hard to find. I paid for my meal and  I waited over an hour for my delivery before calling the restaurant where i was greeted with "Hello?", no name of the restaurant or anything, had to ask if I called the right place. When that was confirmed, they said they were just closing when it clearly states they are open from 11am-10pm. I asked about my order and why I hadn't received it yet, they said they didn't know where the address was. Nobody had called me to figure anything out, so were they planning on just taking my money and not giving me the goods I had paid for? When I finally received my food, the sushi was warm and tasted off...  Never ordering from this place ever again. Would not recommend this establishment to my worst enemy.
Good food, bad service, very bad service. We won't come here no more.

So, I place an order through Seamless & it's accepted. Estimated time of delivery? 5:10. At 5pm I receive a call from the restaurant saying it will take over an hour to deliver from this time. I ask my father-in-law if he's willing to wait. He says 'yes'. I make that clear to the restaurant. They then tell me they actually cannot deliver to my area at all. Why would you give an option? Why would you wait an HOUR to let me know? Never again & I will make it a point to let others know this is how they run a business. Horribly.
